To get started, here are a few handy links:

Install LocalStack:
docs.localstack.cloud/getting-started/installation
Configure an API Key:
docs.localstack.cloud/getting-started/api-key
Check out our quickstart:
docs.localstack.cloud/getting-started/quickstart
Join our community channels:
localstack.cloud/contact
With this, you can set up LocalStack on your machine, utilize a trial plan to start LocalStack with an API key, and run an AWS Serverless application locally without having to connect to a remote cloud provider.

To use LocalStack, we provide ample resources, examples, and sample applications to get started:

User Guides:
docs.localstack.cloud/user-guide
LocalStack Tutorials:
docs.localstack.cloud/tutorials
LocalStack Samples:
github.com/localstack/localstack-pro-samples
LocalStack Blog:
localstack.cloud/blog